Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.25,0:00:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello. Welcome to WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.23,0:00:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Brad Jensen and today we're
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.72,0:00:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be talking about What's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.03,0:00:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,New in Location Technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got three topics that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.73,0:00:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to cover today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.36,0:00:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,First we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.96,0:00:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,some miscellaneous API
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.26,0:00:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements we've made.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.20,0:00:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,After that we'll talk about our
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.59,0:00:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,big change this year, how we've
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.51,0:00:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,revised our authorization and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.41,0:00:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,usage reporting story, and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.60,0:00:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.58,0:00:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll also touch on best
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.95,0:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,practices given the changes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:00:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we've made this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.50,0:01:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a word of warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This presentation is geared
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.75,0:01:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,towards developers that are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.80,0:01:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,already familiar with Core
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.36,0:01:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Location, so if you're new to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.86,0:01:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,our framework, we recommend you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.20,0:01:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,check out our documentation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.38,0:01:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, our session from
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.70,0:01:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,last year has a lot of helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.93,0:01:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,advice for newcomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.77,0:01:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.69,0:01:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For users of our geocoding API,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.96,0:01:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we have some exciting changes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.18,0:01:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.28,0:01:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We've added support for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.45,0:01:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,interoperation with the Contacts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.38,0:01:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.82,0:01:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can now forward geocode a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,CNPostalAddress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.38,0:01:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And additionally, when you get a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.85,0:01:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,CLPlacemark result, you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.02,0:01:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a CNPostalAddress from that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.68,0:01:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,placemark.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is meant to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.61,0:01:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,modern replacement for our old
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.23,0:01:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,support for the Address Book
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.49,0:01:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, you could geocode
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.24,0:01:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,an address dictionary and get an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,address dictionary out of a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.45,0:01:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,placemark.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On platforms where the Contacts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.70,0:01:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,framework is available, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.85,0:01:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,deprecating those address
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.27,0:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,dictionary API's.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.30,0:02:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,However, on tvOS the Contacts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,framework isn't available and so
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.39,0:02:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can continue to use those
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.21,0:02:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,address dictionary API's.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also adding support for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.70,0:02:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,geocoding with a preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,locale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.76,0:02:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't impact which results
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.92,0:02:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you get, only which language
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.73,0:02:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they're returned to you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to note that the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.04,0:02:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,default behavior for Core
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Location's geocoder has always
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.87,0:02:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,been to return results in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.61,0:02:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,user's preferred language.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.17,0:02:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you specify a preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.49,0:02:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,locale, you are overriding the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,user's chosen language
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,preference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That might sound bad, but there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.30,0:02:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are actually times when it makes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if you're making a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.31,0:02:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,travel guide up, you might want
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.52,0:02:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to display text in your app that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.41,0:02:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,matches the text the user would
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.01,0:02:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,see in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.78,0:02:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case you would want to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.94,0:02:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,provide a preferred locale to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the geocoder that produces
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.78,0:02:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,results appropriate for the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.25,0:02:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,region the user is visiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.16,0:03:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We've spent some time improving
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.93,0:03:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our heading updates API as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.40,0:03:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we get to that, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.63,0:03:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,just make sure we all understand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the jargon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Heading refers to the direction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.00,0:03:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are facing, and course
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is the direction you're actually
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.10,0:03:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.41,0:03:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with boats and planes you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.97,0:03:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to see a disconnect between
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.58,0:03:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,heading and course due to wind
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.65,0:03:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or sea currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.67,0:03:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With cars, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you almost never see a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,meaningful difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.92,0:03:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,heading and course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.37,0:03:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if there are very strong
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.99,0:03:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,winds that push the car to one
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,side or the other, the driver
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.09,0:03:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will tend to compensate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.54,0:03:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't want to get pushed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.79,0:03:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of their lane, or even
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.84,0:03:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,worse, off the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very convenient
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.28,0:03:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,observation because if we're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.65,0:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,computing GPS estimates, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.09,0:03:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,very likely to have a good
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,estimate of the device's course,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.91,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but sometimes computing the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,heading can be a little bit more
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we're able to accurately
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,estimate the heading of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.59,0:04:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,device, it might not be the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.32,0:04:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,right heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, let's suppose the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.42,0:04:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,user is navigating in their car
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.21,0:04:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and they've mounted their iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.81,0:04:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to their dashboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a very good chance that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.32,0:04:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they've angled their iPhone to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.70,0:04:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,face themselves, but when they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,do that, they introduce a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.66,0:04:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,disconnect between the heading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.10,0:04:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of their car and the heading of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.87,0:04:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,their iPhone, but when they're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,navigating, they'd really like
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.38,0:04:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the heading of their car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.34,0:04:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, we just found a really
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.82,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,good way to estimate the heading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.93,0:04:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We can use the course of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.13,0:04:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.53,0:04:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So in iOS 11 Core Location will
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,now automatically detect
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.62,0:04:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,situations where heading and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,course should probably be in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.04,0:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement and it will leverage
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.92,0:04:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,course information to provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.78,0:04:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,more accurate heading update.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.88,0:04:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to note that this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior is fully automatic and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.39,0:04:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,always on when you use Core
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:04:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Location's heading API.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.25,0:05:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're creating an app for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.17,0:05:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,planes or boats or augmented
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,reality, then you probably want
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to use Core Motion's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,CMDeviceMotion API instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our detection logic is very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.17,0:05:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,good, but it's not flawless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.82,0:05:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There are times when it will
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.97,0:05:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,make the wrong call.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,about their API, they had a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,session this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.21,0:05:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's definitely worth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,checking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.04,0:05:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also spent a lot of time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,improving our indoor positioning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.13,0:05:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.24,0:05:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As you saw in the keynote, Maps
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will now display floor plans for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,many indoor venues throughout
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.03,0:05:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.38,0:05:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,At these venues any app that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.11,0:05:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,requests best accuracy location
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,will automatically receive our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.49,0:05:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,high accuracy indoor location
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.48,0:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,estimates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.80,0:05:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We have four exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements that I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,share with you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we've improved the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,accuracy of our estimates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.34,0:06:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our estimates are GPS quality or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.37,0:06:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.14,0:06:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, we've improved the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.90,0:06:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,responsiveness of our indoor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.57,0:06:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,positioning system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.92,0:06:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When the user first enters a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.45,0:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,venue, you'll start to receive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,those indoor estimates much more
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly than you did in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also improved how quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we detect floor transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get notified of the new
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,floor more quickly than you did
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.73,0:06:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've improved the availability.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.66,0:06:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't just mean the number
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.01,0:06:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of venues that Core Location
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.93,0:06:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,supports.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.79,0:06:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user wanders into a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.52,0:06:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,region of the venue that maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't been surveyed, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,still get quality indoor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.55,0:06:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,estimates through Core Location.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've improved the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.81,0:06:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,interoperability of the indoor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.44,0:06:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,positioning system with wireless
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,accessories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.98,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if the user is, say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,streaming Beats 1 to their
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,AirPods, you'll still receive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.38,0:06:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,quality indoor location
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:06:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,estimates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.08,0:07:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For watchOS we're making our
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.18,0:07:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous background location
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.78,0:07:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,API available.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've probably already heard
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.19,0:07:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about this API, but just in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.64,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,case, this API allows your app
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to receive location updates even
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as it enters the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.51,0:07:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in watchOS 3 it was
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.44,0:07:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,possible to get very similar
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality using a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of Core Location and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,HealthKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.21,0:07:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,An HKWorkoutSession would allow
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.54,0:07:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your app to continue receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,location updates even if your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,app was in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we wanted to allow you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.17,0:07:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to create new location-based
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences that weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.80,0:07:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily workout related, and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're bringing our general
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.95,0:07:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.58,0:07:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,location API to watchOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.16,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Our usual guidance still
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,applies.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.26,0:07:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a fairly power expensive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.27,0:08:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,API and so you should think
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.01,0:08:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,twice before using it, but if
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you're creating, say, a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.16,0:08:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation app or a fitness app,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,location is almost certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.12,0:08:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.56,0:08:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to ensure that this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,functionality was exposed in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.81,0:08:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,only one place, and so in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.99,0:08:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS 4 HKWorkoutSessions no
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.25,0:08:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,longer give your app access to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,location in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.40,0:08:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Legacy apps will continue to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.58,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,work, but when you link against
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the watchOS 4 SDK, you must
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.52,0:08:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt the continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.94,0:08:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,location API.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, your app will be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.18,0:08:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to access the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.62,0:08:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.59,0:08:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, it's very easy to adopt
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.73,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our API.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are simply three easy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.96,0:08:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you enable the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.15,0:08:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,LocationUpdates background mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.41,0:08:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply navigate to the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.86,0:08:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Capabilities tab in Xcode,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll down to Background Modes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.90,0:08:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and check the Location Updates
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:08:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,box.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:09:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, you need to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.73,0:09:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,allowsBackgroundLocationUpdates
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.46,0:09:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,property to True on your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Location Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.50,0:09:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We recommend you only do this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,after the user has performed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.89,0:09:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,some action which requires --
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.97,0:09:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting a little ahead of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.58,0:09:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.23,0:09:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We recommend you do this only
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.87,0:09:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,after the user has initiated the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,workout session or the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.19,0:09:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation session.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.44,0:09:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't accidentally
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.76,0:09:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,start the continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,location session before you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.27,0:09:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,meant to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, you simply call
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,startUpdatingLocation while your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.33,0:09:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,app is in the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.00,0:09:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When your app enters the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,background, Core Location will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.62,0:09:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,keep your app running and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to deliver location
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.03,0:09:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.03,0:09:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,workout apps, we have some
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,advice to help you create the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,best possible experience for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,your users.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.92,0:09:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we recommend you continue
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.14,0:09:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to use HealthKit, even though
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.00,0:09:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it's possible to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.34,0:09:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,fitness app that doesn't use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.80,0:10:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,HealthKit or HKWorkoutSession,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.67,0:10:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,doing so will make your app miss
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.69,0:10:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,out on a lot of special tuning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.92,0:10:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we've put into Core Location for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,workout scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So continue to use HealthKit and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.65,0:10:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,HKWorkoutSession.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, if you know that your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.83,0:10:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,user is in a pedestrian workout,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we recommend you use CMPedometer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.94,0:10:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to estimate how far the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.95,0:10:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In some environments it can be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.23,0:10:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,very tricky to accurately
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.81,0:10:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,estimate the user's location,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.18,0:10:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and if the user goes through a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.70,0:10:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,run in one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.67,0:10:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,environments, you'll find it's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.29,0:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,even harder to accurately
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.10,0:10:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,estimate how far they have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.54,0:10:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.90,0:10:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you know they're in a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.96,0:10:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,pedestrian workout and you use
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,CMPedometer, your app won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.25,0:10:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,affected by those difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. That's the miscellaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.67,0:10:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.65,0:10:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get to the big one;
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization and use of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:10:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:10:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of time iterating
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,on how Core Location's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.21,0:11:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization and usage
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.27,0:11:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting works, and we've got
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.21,0:11:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,some exciting changes that we
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.54,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,think your users are going to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,love.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's quickly review how
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.05,0:11:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it all works.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.72,0:11:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Core Location supports two
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization modes; WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.45,0:11:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and Always.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.60,0:11:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization allows your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,app to access the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.10,0:11:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,location anytime your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.29,0:11:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,running.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.96,0:11:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, Always authorized
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.86,0:11:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,apps can use our background
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.40,0:11:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring API's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These allow your app to get
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.66,0:11:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,runtime and receive information
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.36,0:11:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when various location-based
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.09,0:11:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,events have occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.61,0:11:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the region
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring API will launch your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.66,0:11:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,app whenever the user arrives at
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or departs from a region of your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.28,0:11:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,choosing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.32,0:11:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The WhenInUse authorization mode
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.61,0:11:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,allows your app to access the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.52,0:11:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,user's location anytime your app
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually if your app is in use,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.92,0:12:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that means it's in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.67,0:12:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground, but that's not
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.48,0:12:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,always the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.22,0:12:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if you're using the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous background location
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.45,0:12:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,API, on iOS Core Location will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,draw a blue bar, a blue
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.31,0:12:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,double-height status bar at the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,top of the screen, reminding the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,user that the app is still
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.32,0:12:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,running and still accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,their location, and in that way
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.25,0:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is still considered in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.96,0:12:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We introduced the WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.74,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization mode because we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.00,0:12:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to allow users a greater
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.47,0:12:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,level of control over how apps
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.63,0:12:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,access their private data.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And users love this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.49,0:12:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They love knowing that apps can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.81,0:12:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,only access their location at
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.47,0:12:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,times when they want it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we think this represents a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.21,0:12:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,great balance between the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.67,0:12:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ability to control how your app
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.39,0:12:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,accesses their location and your
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.56,0:12:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,ability to create compelling app
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.23,0:12:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences for the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.69,0:12:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we introduced the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.11,0:12:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization mode the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.72,0:13:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,response has been tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.17,0:13:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost 80 percent of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,location-using apps on iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.64,0:13:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,support WhenInUse authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.31,0:13:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A mere 21 percent have chosen to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.23,0:13:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,require Always authorization
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.67,0:13:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Users love the WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization mode, and thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.49,0:13:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to your efforts, they almost
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,always have it available to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.95,0:13:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We think this is fantastic, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to see if we could do
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's look at some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons why an app might choose
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.17,0:13:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to require Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.42,0:13:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We think that one of the common
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons is the developer's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.86,0:13:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,simply confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.52,0:13:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It turns out that many apps
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.06,0:13:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which require Always
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.16,0:13:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization don't actually use
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.59,0:13:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,any of our background monitoring
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,API's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.03,0:13:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very likely that these apps
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,would continue to function just
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fine if they were granted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.96,0:13:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.78,0:14:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the user encounters one
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.31,0:14:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of these apps, they don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.06,0:14:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't see the app source
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.65,0:14:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.05,0:14:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know that it won't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,monitor them all day and so they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.36,0:14:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have to treat it as though it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.65,0:14:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,will, and this creates a very
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.38,0:14:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,poor user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.29,0:14:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a second reason we think
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that many developers choose to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.55,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,require Always authorization is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they're simply trying to give
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.16,0:14:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,their users the best possible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.32,0:14:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.48,0:14:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,See, not all features can be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.06,0:14:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,implemented reasonably with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.42,0:14:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.88,0:14:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Some basically require Always
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization, and we think that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.07,0:14:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,these developers simply want to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.85,0:14:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ensure that their users have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,access to all the best that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,their app has to offer, but this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.67,0:14:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,makes for a very poor user
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.46,0:14:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for the users that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,don't wish to grant the app
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.49,0:14:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.52,0:14:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They are forced to choose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.73,0:14:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,between granting the app Always,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.03,0:14:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which is more than they would
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.72,0:14:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like in this example, or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.95,0:15:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,granting it Never, which means
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't get to benefit from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.57,0:15:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,any of the app's location-based
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.99,0:15:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.03,0:15:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And their final openings to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,grant it Always and then revoke
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.09,0:15:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that authorization after they're
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.92,0:15:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,done using the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, the user is not
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.29,0:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,having a great time with this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So for iOS 11 we're asking all
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.26,0:15:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,developers with Always
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,requesting apps to additionally
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.17,0:15:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,support the WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This change is both retroactive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.34,0:15:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and forward-looking, so when the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.24,0:15:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,user updates to iOS 11, they
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.03,0:15:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will be able to authorize any
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.51,0:15:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,app that requests Always
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.10,0:15:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization the WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.11,0:15:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization mode instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you link against the iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,SDK, you must provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.33,0:15:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUseUsageDescription.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.73,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, your app will be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:15:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to request Always
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.59,0:16:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.58,0:16:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, when your app
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,requests Always authorization,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we will additionally display an
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.10,0:16:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,option to grant your app
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.38,0:16:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.79,0:16:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,With these new three option
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,prompts we have a new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.18,0:16:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription string as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app needs to provide an
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,AlwaysAndWhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.43,0:16:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.43,0:16:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Since this is a different key
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,your app must provide it when
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.54,0:16:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you link against the new iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,SDK.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For apps linked against iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.75,0:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and later, Core Location will
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.65,0:16:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,not use the old NSLocationAlways
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.26,0:16:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's talk a little bit about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,best practices; how does this
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.16,0:16:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,change things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.17,0:16:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For apps that want Always
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization we recommend you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.73,0:16:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,provide all three keys, even
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.97,0:16:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that NSLocationAlways
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.71,0:16:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription that I just
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.02,0:17:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,said we won't use.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.32,0:17:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason why is if you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,want to deploy your app on a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,device that's running iOS 10 or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.12,0:17:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier, you need to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.79,0:17:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,strings that it can understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you should continue to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.01,0:17:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,provide that NSLocationAlways
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.08,0:17:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.50,0:17:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, your AlwaysAndWhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.95,0:17:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription should help the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.35,0:17:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,user choose between Always and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.16,0:17:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.10,0:17:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use it in context where
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the two options
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.80,0:17:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,presented to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So your description should
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.27,0:17:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,explain to the user what
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,features will be enabled if they
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,select WhenInUse authorization,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.68,0:17:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then what additional
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,features they'll receive if they
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,choose to grant your app Always
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.53,0:17:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.24,0:17:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,For all apps we recommend that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.94,0:17:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you only request authorization
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.33,0:17:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when you really need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.06,0:17:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wait to request
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.39,0:17:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization until the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,performed some action which
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,requires access to the location,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.30,0:18:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then when the prompt appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the user will have all the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,context, all this intuitive
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.36,0:18:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding that they need in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.30,0:18:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,order to understand why your app
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.44,0:18:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,wants access to location.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.76,0:18:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes it much more likely
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that they'll actually grant your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,app authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For apps that request Always
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization, there's a little
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.94,0:18:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,bit more to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.80,0:18:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We recommend you request
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.38,0:18:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.22,0:18:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Requesting WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization is a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.53,0:18:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,easier, not asking as much from
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the user, but there's more to it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.09,0:18:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.99,0:18:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We think your app should make
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.57,0:18:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse its base experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.70,0:18:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing users encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.13,0:18:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, after the user has had a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.61,0:18:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,chance to explore your app and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.05,0:18:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,get to know all of its features,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.55,0:18:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when they discover that one that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.82,0:18:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,requires Always, they'll try to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,turn it on and at that point
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,your app can display a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:18:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,transition prompt that requests
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.63,0:18:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization on top of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the WhenInUse authorization you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When this prompt appears, the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.22,0:19:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,user will once again have that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitive context they need in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.32,0:19:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,order to understand why your app
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.93,0:19:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is requesting Always and they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.35,0:19:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,be much more likely to grant it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the user first launches
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.06,0:19:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your app, you'll have an
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.75,0:19:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,undetermined authorization
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.11,0:19:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.70,0:19:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,From here you can request either
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.99,0:19:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization or
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.47,0:19:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what happens if you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.37,0:19:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,request WhenInUse authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Core Location will display our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.29,0:19:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization prompt,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.97,0:19:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,using your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.92,0:19:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUseUsageDescription in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.97,0:19:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,body of the alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.26,0:19:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on the user's choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.69,0:19:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll end up with either
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization or no
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.69,0:19:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.51,0:19:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After this point the user can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.82,0:19:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,freely go to settings and adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's authorization value
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.69,0:19:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to whatever they like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.52,0:20:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the user has chosen to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.22,0:20:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,grant your app WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.46,0:20:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization, which they
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.92,0:20:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,probably will if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.98,0:20:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,following our best practices,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.92,0:20:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you can additionally request
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.38,0:20:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.53,0:20:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When this happens, Core Location
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.11,0:20:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,will display a transition prompt
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and will use that new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.69,0:20:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,AlwaysAndWhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription string.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.98,0:20:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,From here the user can either
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.92,0:20:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,grant your app Always
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization or keep it at its
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.08,0:20:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,current WhenInUse value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After your app has requested
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.34,0:20:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.84,0:20:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to request any further
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.52,0:20:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,prompts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.14,0:20:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go back to the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.12,0:20:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you had requested Always
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization at the very
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning, right when your app
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.18,0:20:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,launches, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.14,0:20:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The user will see this prompt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.64,0:20:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll see a WhenInUse option,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.85,0:20:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll see an Always option,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.50,0:20:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll see a Don't Allow
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,option.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.24,0:20:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:20:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,why your app wants access to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.88,0:20:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,location all the time, if they
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have that context that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we're recommending you provide,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.14,0:21:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,then it's very likely they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,grant your app WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.90,0:21:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization instead, and if
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that happens, you won't be able
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.06,0:21:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to initiate a transition prompt
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.86,0:21:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and this prompt also uses
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.72,0:21:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that new combined
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.19,0:21:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,UsageDescription key.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.53,0:21:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Before we move on from
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.49,0:21:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization, I'm excited to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.43,0:21:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,announce that on watchOS 4 Core
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.67,0:21:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Location will support prompting
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for authorization directly on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.19,0:21:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the watch itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.10,0:21:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously --
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously, if you tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.15,0:21:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,request authorization, watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.54,0:21:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,would alert the user that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a prompt waiting for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.62,0:21:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,them on their phone and they
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.92,0:21:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would have to go over to their
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,phone and respond to it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.87,0:21:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't got this all finished
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.95,0:21:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not in the seed you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.36,0:21:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,received earlier this week, but
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.01,0:21:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we do expect it to land in a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.21,0:21:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,future seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's done, all you'll have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.79,0:21:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to do is rebuild your app and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.69,0:22:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the next time you install it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.75,0:22:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you should start to see these
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.84,0:22:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,standalone prompts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.91,0:22:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.49,0:22:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about usage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.88,0:22:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.89,0:22:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, let's talk about how
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.18,0:22:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it worked in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.23,0:22:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Core Location would report the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.86,0:22:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,location usage of your app based
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.96,0:22:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on which services you were
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.36,0:22:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,using.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.36,0:22:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Most services would result in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.29,0:22:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your app getting a solid arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.13,0:22:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the status bar and in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.36,0:22:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.86,0:22:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you used the region
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.87,0:22:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring service, you would
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,instead get a hollow arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.33,0:22:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, if you were a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.83,0:22:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorized app and you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.20,0:22:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,requested the continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.30,0:22:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,background location service, we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.98,0:22:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,would draw this blue
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.17,0:22:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,double-height status bar that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.23,0:22:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've mentioned a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.05,0:22:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We felt this system was very
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It served us well for a long
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.97,0:22:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,time, but we thought there was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.37,0:22:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.44,0:23:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This system over-represents the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.65,0:23:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy exposure of some of our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.31,0:23:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,API's.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.90,0:23:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's compare two apps; one of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.38,0:23:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,them using the significant
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.94,0:23:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,location change monitoring
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.28,0:23:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,service, and the other one using
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.17,0:23:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.44,0:23:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,location service.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.76,0:23:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of these apps will have a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.02,0:23:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,solid arrow continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.78,0:23:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the app using
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.36,0:23:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,significant location change
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.59,0:23:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring is going to receive
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.59,0:23:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,far less location information
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.30,0:23:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,than the app using continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.81,0:23:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,background location.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.22,0:23:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The app using significant
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.91,0:23:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,location change monitoring is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.13,0:23:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,only going to get updates when
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.45,0:23:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the device has actually moved a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.16,0:23:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,significant distance, and even
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.84,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then, there's a rate limit on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,top.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the app receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous background location
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.30,0:23:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to get far more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,location information, but they
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.31,0:23:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,have the exact same usage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.94,0:23:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.76,0:23:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we thought that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.59,0:23:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorized apps were
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.89,0:23:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,missing out on the blue bar as a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.94,0:23:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.99,0:24:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose you have a navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.57,0:24:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,app that is granted Always
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.57,0:24:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.97,0:24:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user is in a navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.61,0:24:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,session, they probably want to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.30,0:24:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to return to that very
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.64,0:24:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly after briefly using
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.37,0:24:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,another app, but in iOS 10
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.19,0:24:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorized apps don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.81,0:24:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this blue double-height status
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.19,0:24:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We felt that these problems made
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.37,0:24:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it difficult for users to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.82,0:24:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly interpret how apps
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.04,0:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,were using their location.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.33,0:24:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, let's consider
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.53,0:24:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,those two apps again; the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.94,0:24:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous background location
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.21,0:24:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the significant location
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.33,0:24:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,change monitoring app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.61,0:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose the user goes for a run
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.19,0:24:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with the continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.25,0:24:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,location app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.50,0:24:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll go on the run, they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.32,0:24:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,come back, they'll see the solid
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.45,0:24:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow the whole time, and when
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.51,0:24:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they look at their map, they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.39,0:24:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,see every twist and turn they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.73,0:24:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,took.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.81,0:24:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When they install that app that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.05,0:24:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uses significant location change
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.60,0:24:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring, they'll see the same
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.07,0:24:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, a solid arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.07,0:24:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as the user is aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.20,0:24:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,this app is probably receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.90,0:24:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the same amount of information
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.60,0:25:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as their run tracking app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.70,0:25:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if users are misinterpreting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.20,0:25:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,our signals, we decided the best
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.71,0:25:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,way to fix this was to adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.56,0:25:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,how we indicate location usage.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.14,0:25:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a new policy and we
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.66,0:25:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,think you're going to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.60,0:25:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We've changed how the arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.88,0:25:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.51,0:25:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When your app requests location
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.48,0:25:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,information from Core Location,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.63,0:25:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we display a hollow arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.99,0:25:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you actually receive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.30,0:25:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,location information, we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.45,0:25:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,switch that to a solid arrow for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.42,0:25:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.49,0:25:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go through an example of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.86,0:25:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,how that actually works in just
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.16,0:25:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.91,0:25:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, as you probably
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.21,0:25:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,guessed, we're bringing the blue
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.45,0:25:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,double-height status bar to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.22,0:25:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorized apps that use
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.06,0:25:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the continuous background
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.11,0:25:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,location service.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.75,0:25:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we expect that this new
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.46,0:25:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,policy will help users
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.68,0:25:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,understand your app's location
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.99,0:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,usage more better.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.04,0:26:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.80,0:26:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Previously we had that hollow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.56,0:26:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow behavior and users came to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.59,0:26:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that the hollow arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.04,0:26:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,indicated that an app was using
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.65,0:26:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,location in the background, but
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.49,0:26:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't continuously receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.16,0:26:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.54,0:26:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was receiving them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.96,0:26:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,potentially intermittently or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.23,0:26:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,only when specific events
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.65,0:26:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred, and so they understood
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.27,0:26:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that this arrow represented
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.96,0:26:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,low-powered background
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.17,0:26:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.85,0:26:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're now extending that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.89,0:26:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding to all of Core
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.82,0:26:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Location's API's, and we think
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.87,0:26:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this is much better for you as
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.70,0:26:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the developers as well because
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.57,0:26:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,now users will be able to see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.45,0:26:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly how much, or as the case
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.84,0:26:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,may be, how little information
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.58,0:26:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is actually receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.14,0:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's running in the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.88,0:26:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,background.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.25,0:26:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're using our background
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.48,0:26:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,monitoring API's, you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.25,0:26:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have a hollow arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.56,0:26:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,more and a solid arrow less, and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.40,0:27:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we think this will help users
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.04,0:27:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that your app is not
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.88,0:27:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,actually receiving every single
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.92,0:27:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,step, every twist and turn
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.45,0:27:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout their day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.35,0:27:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So let's look at how that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.03,0:27:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow works in practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.38,0:27:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a test iPhone and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.58,0:27:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it's currently at AT&T Park and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.67,0:27:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,let's suppose an app is using
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.03,0:27:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Visit monitoring service.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.88,0:27:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The device has been stationary
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.11,0:27:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,here for a long time and so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.61,0:27:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we're displaying a hollow arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.48,0:27:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the status bar because Core
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.90,0:27:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Location is not delivering new
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.20,0:27:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,information to the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.89,0:27:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, once the user gets up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.06,0:27:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and starts moving towards, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.05,0:27:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,say the Ferry Building, Core
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.83,0:27:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Location will detect that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.25,0:27:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,departure event and alert the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.58,0:27:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.72,0:27:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That will result in a solid
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.05,0:27:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow appearing in the status
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.67,0:27:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,bar for a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.75,0:27:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As the user continues their
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.15,0:27:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,journey the arrow will return to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.06,0:27:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,its hollow state and it will
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.72,0:28:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,remain hollow until Core
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.68,0:28:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Location detects an arrival
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.49,0:28:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,event.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.59,0:28:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,After it detects that, it will
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.18,0:28:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,launch the app once again and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.48,0:28:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the app will receive a solid
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.12,0:28:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,arrow that will linger for a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.57,0:28:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of seconds, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.17,0:28:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,after that it will remain hollow
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.44,0:28:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,until the user departs from that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.09,0:28:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.64,0:28:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We really hope that this new
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.66,0:28:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,policy helps users better
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.17,0:28:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,understand exactly when and how
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.77,0:28:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps are accessing their
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.86,0:28:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,location, and we think that it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.96,0:28:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,will result in users no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.39,0:28:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,blaming your app for things it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.10,0:28:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not actually doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.44,0:28:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we've got for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.13,0:28:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And just to recap, there are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.70,0:28:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,three important points I want
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.91,0:28:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.76,0:28:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, users have more control
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.23,0:28:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,over how your app accesses their
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.62,0:28:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.82,0:28:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically, users can now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.35,0:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,grant your app WhenInUse
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.59,0:28:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization if you request
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.25,0:28:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.77,0:29:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we always recommend that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.23,0:29:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you communicate with the user
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and help them understand why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.00,0:29:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,your app wants access to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,location, but apps that request
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.33,0:29:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization have an
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.92,0:29:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,even greater responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.48,0:29:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.96,0:29:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,why your app wants access to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.58,0:29:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization, then
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.61,0:29:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not likely to grant it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.87,0:29:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.34,0:29:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They're likely to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.28,0:29:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.88,0:29:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have that greater
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.89,0:29:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility if you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.51,0:29:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,receive Always authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.28,0:29:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best way we think that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.25,0:29:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can communicate with the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.38,0:29:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,user to help them understand why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.46,0:29:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you're asking for Always
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.36,0:29:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,authorization, the best way to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.92,0:29:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,maximize your chances of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.86,0:29:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,receiving Always authorization
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.30,0:29:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the user is to give them
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.17,0:29:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that context that I talked about
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.97,0:29:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.91,0:29:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them that intuitive
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.95,0:29:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.60,0:29:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them explore your app with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.14,0:29:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,WhenInUse authorization, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.14,0:29:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,then when they try to enable
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.83,0:29:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that feature that requires
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.23,0:29:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Always authorization, then you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.28,0:29:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,initiate that transition prompt
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.11,0:29:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will almost certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.60,0:29:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,grant your app authorization at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.98,0:30:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.39,0:30:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.28,0:30:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to learn more, we
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.70,0:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have some supplementary material
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.00,0:30:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,online.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.76,0:30:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We've updated our PotLoc app,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.66,0:30:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for example, so you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.00,0:30:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that's got some new goodies for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.25,0:30:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.44,0:30:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We also recommend you check out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.58,0:30:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these related sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.51,0:30:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already mentioned the Core
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.82,0:30:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Motion one, but the Privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.63,0:30:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,session from earlier this week
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.54,0:30:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,was also very good and it has a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.83,0:30:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of great advice to help you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.20,0:30:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,build an app that respects the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.63,0:30:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,user's privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.68,0:30:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your time, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.90,0:30:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hope you enjoy the rest of WWDC.
